{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s26_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b1ad37",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 60-year-old man has pain in his lower thoracic spine that began 10 days ago following a urinary tract infection. Temperature is 37.9 °C (100.2 °F). Point tenderness of the lower thoracic spine is present."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"18abeb",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose acute hematogenous osteomyelitis of the vertebral spine. For management, obtain urine and blood cultures and spine MRI."
]
}
]
}
]
